All participants (11 participants at baseline and 10 participants at the 2-month follow-up) were scanned on the same 3 T GE MR750 scanner (General Electric, Milwaukee, United States) at Cornell University MRI Facility using a 32-channel receive-only phased-array head coil. The study was approved by the Institutional Review Board of Cornell University, and all participants gave written informed consent. All methods described in this manuscript were carried out in accordance with the approved guidelines. The scan began with a three-plane localizer to define the anatomy of interest. Sagittal T1-weighted magnetization prepared rapid gradient echo (MPRAGE) images covering the whole brain were acquired in 5 min 30 s with parameters: 176 slices with matrix size: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
